1. Delete all steps after "Grouped Rows" in the Applid Steps pane in the Power Query Editor
2. Change the aggregation method for the TotalStock to calculate the average instead of the sum of the advanced editor, also, change the name of the TotalStock column to AverageStock
3. Click Done once the above changes have been applied
4. Expand the Grouped column, selecting "ProductID", "ProductName" and "UnitsInStock". Make sure to uncheck "Use original column name as prefix"
5. Add a custom column called StockPercentDeviation that calculates the ratio between each product's stock and the average category stock for each product then format the column as a percentage
6. Filter the data to only contain products with less than 10% of the average stock for their category
